Sight radius: 3.8" 96mm

The P-32 has six main component groups: barrel, slide, firing mechanism, grip, and magazine. The barrel is made of SAE 4140 ordnance steel, heat treated to 48 HRC. The slide is also 4140 steel, and contains the firing pin and the extractor. The rectangular frame is machined from solid 7075-T6 aluminum and houses the firing mechanism. The trigger connects via a transfer bar to the hammer. The hammer is driven by a novel free floating extension spring. The light weight firing pin transmits the energy of the hammer to ignite the primer. After firing, the hammer block holds the hammer away from the firing pin, providing a mechanical safety.

title: For Sale:  Gun Trust Services - Hanna Law P.C.
location: Serving all of Colorado, Denver, Colorado
postcontent:
Hanna Law, P.C. offers gun trust services to all of Colorado, and offers two levels of service: Basic Gun Trust for $225 and Comprehensive Gun Trust for $500

Are you looking to build an SBR? Maybe you're purchasing your first suppressor? A gun trust offers you a great deal of convenience when you own these items.

Hanna Law, P.C. is a different kind of law firm, specializing in firearms trusts. We do not operate on a normal business week schedule, but can accommodate your needs on your schedule. We are available during the day and in the evening as well as weekends.

We understand that buying an NFA item can be a lengthy process, so we strive to offer great service with a short turnaround.

We offer two levels of trust:
Basic Gun Trust $225 - fast and easy, convenient for those who do not wish to speak at great lengths with the attorney. If you e-mail your info and give us a call, everything can be handled in person very quickly. Notary services provided at time of delivery.

Comprehensive Gun Trust $500 - Also fast, however, the attorney will meet with you and discuss all the provisions of the trust. If you do not like specific provisions, need clarification on certain provisions, or would like to add or remove provisions, this is the level for you. Generally it takes 1.5-2 hours of face time with the attorney to go over the entire document. Notary services provided during meeting. This is a good option for those who are unfamiliar with firearms trusts, and demand extensive clarification. Some people are a bit nervous when starting their NFA item collection, and face-time with an informed attorney can put some of these concerns to rest.

For various reasons, you may wish to also put your Title I (regular) firearms into your trust as well. We also offer this service.

We wish you the best on your journey into the land of SBR's, AOW's, SBS's, and suppressors. They can be great home defense weapons, and sure are a whole lot of fun to shoot at the range. We hope to hear from you soon. Feel free to call at REDACTED. Leave us a voicemail with your number and a good time to return your call, and we will get back to you promptly. You can also e-mail us at REDACTED.

title: For Sale:  Gun Trust Services - Hanna Law P.C.
location: Serving all of Colorado, Fort Collins, Colorado
postcontent:
Hanna Law, P.C. offers gun trust services to all of Colorado, and offers two levels of service: Basic Gun Trust for $225 and Comprehensive Gun Trust for $500

Are you looking to build an SBR? Maybe you're purchasing your first suppressor? A gun trust offers you a great deal of convenience when you own these items.

Hanna Law, P.C. is a different kind of law firm, specializing in firearms trusts. We do not operate on a normal business week schedule, but can accommodate your needs on your schedule. We are available during the day and in the evening as well as weekends.

We understand that buying an NFA item can be a lengthy process, so we strive to offer great service with a short turnaround.

We offer two levels of trust:
Basic Gun Trust $225 - fast and easy, convenient for those who do not wish to speak at great lengths with the attorney. If you e-mail your info and give us a call, everything can be handled in person very quickly. Notary services provided at time of delivery.

Comprehensive Gun Trust $500 - Also fast, however, the attorney will meet with you and discuss all the provisions of the trust. If you do not like specific provisions, need clarification on certain provisions, or would like to add or remove provisions, this is the level for you. Generally it takes 1.5-2 hours of face time with the attorney to go over the entire document. Notary services provided during meeting. This is a good option for those who are unfamiliar with firearms trusts, and demand extensive clarification. Some people are a bit nervous when starting their NFA item collection, and face-time with an informed attorney can put some of these concerns to rest.

For various reasons, you may wish to also put your Title I (regular) firearms into your trust as well. We also offer this service.

We wish you the best on your journey into the land of SBR's, AOW's, SBS's, and suppressors. They can be great home defense weapons, and sure are a whole lot of fun to shoot at the range. We hope to hear from you soon. Feel free to call at 720-568-0564. Leave us a voicemail with your number and a good time to return your call, and we will get back to you promptly. You can also e-mail us at info@hannalawpc.com.

title: For Sale:  NEW Silencerco Warlock 22 Silencer Suppressor
postcontent: Check us out online!  www.54-17arms.com Brand new Silencerco Warlock 22 Silencer Suppressor with thread mount. No credit card fees and shipping to your local FFL is FREE!  Price does not include the NFA tax stamp or local sales tax.  Also, with the purchase of this suppressor, we can assist you in creating a basic living trust!  A living trust will speed up the transfer process.  Let us know if you have questions.  The Warlock 22 was created for maximum sound suppression in a lightweight aluminum package. The Warlock 22 has minimal first round pop for optimal discretion. From varmint hunting to plinking, this 22 suppressor will ensure quiet success. The Warlock 22 has a unique CTA baffle design for easy disassembly and user serviceability, which is very important for any .22LR silencer. Because the .22LR round is not copper jacketed, molten lead and carbon debris will explode into the silencer when the projectile exits the muzzle. After some time it is possible for a .22 suppressor to fill completely with lead and become heavy and ineffective. To avoid this issue they must be disassembled for cleaning and regularly maintained. Most .22 silencers on the market can be disassembled for cleaning, however they require cleaning every 50 to 200 rounds or often times they will fuse together and they are unable to come apart. When the lead and carbon debris adhere to the inner wall of the silencer tube and fill the spaces between the baffles and the tube, there is simply too much build up of fouling and lead to remove the tube from most .22LR silencers on the market. The Warlock 22 has the unique CTA baffle design that keeps the carbon and lead debris from reaching the silencer tube allowing it to be disassembled easily. Check out this video showing how easy it is to clean! WARLOCK 22 CALIBER: .22 LR WEIGHT: 3.0 OZ DIAMETER: 1.000” LENGTH: 6.00” SOUND LEVEL: 117 dB (tested with Walther P22, CCI Standard Velocity) FINISH: Hard Coat Anodized MATERIALS: Baffles & End Caps: 7075 T6 Aluminum Tube: 6061 T6 Aluminum Thread Mount: 17-4 Stainless Steel FEATURES: User Serviceable with CTA Baffles Lifetime Warranty Lightweight O-Ring engagement to keep barrel threads clean and the silencer securely mounted MSRP: $299

title: For Sale:  NEW Silencerco Sparrow 22 Silencer Suppressor
postcontent: Check us out online!  www.54-17arms.com Brand new Silencerco Sparrow 22 Silencer Suppressor with thread mount. No credit card fees and shipping to your local FFL is FREE!  Price does not include the NFA tax stamp or local sales tax.  Also, with the purchase of this suppressor, we can assist you in creating a basic living trust!  A living trust will speed up the transfer process.  Let us know if you have questions.  The Sparrow 22 is the first silencer in the world to offer the patented multi part containment (MPC) technology, which allows the Sparrow 22 to be easily disassembled for cleaning and maintenance after heavy use. Because the .22 LR round is not copper jacketed, molten lead and carbon debris will explode into the silencer when the projectile exits the muzzle. After some time, it is possible for a .22 suppressor to fill completely with lead and become heavy and ineffective. To avoid this issue, .22 silencers must be disassembled for cleaning and regular maintenance. Until Silencerco introduced the Sparrow 22, the only .22 silencers that could be disassembled for cleaning required a cleaning every 50 to 200 rounds. However, often the components of those silencers would be fused together and unable to come apart. Competitor products on the market have baffles in their .22 silencers that must be removed by twisting the outer tube around the baffles and/or sliding the outer tube off of the baffles. When the lead and carbon debris adhere to the inner wall of the outer tube and fill the spaces between the baffles and the outer tube, there is simply too much buildup of fouling and lead to remove the outer tube in that manner. SPARROW 22 CALIBER: .22 LR .17 HMR .22 MAG .22 WMR .22 Hornet 5.7×28 FN WEIGHT: 6.5 OZ DIAMETER: 1.062” LENGTH: 5.08” SOUND REDUCTION: 41dB FINISH: Black Oxide MATERIALS: Alloy Steel Heat Treated 17-4 PH Stainless Steel Mount: 1⁄2×28 threads FEATURES: User Serviceable Multi-Part Containment Technology Full Auto Rated on .22 LR O-Ring engagement to keep barrel threads clean and the silencer securely mounted Serialized outer tube is protected Stainless Steel is Chemical and Solvent Resistant Lifetime Warranty MSRP: $499
